==English==

===Etymology===
Variant of {{term|walk the walk}}, arising out of challenge: "You can talk the talk,can you walk the talk"

===Verb===
{{head|en|verb|head=to [[walk]] the [[talk]]}}

# {{context|idiomatic|US|lang=en}} To do what one said one could do, or would do, not just making [[empty promises]].

